name: Jendela Di Bali Villa near Ubud Bali
address: Jl. Benawah - Petak Kaja, Petak Kaja, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80515, Indonesia
review 1: By far one of the best experiences ever in terms of hospitality, value of money, and overall absolutely gorgeous setting. The staff is super friendly and so cute. You get the whole estate to yourself. It's located in a smaller quiet village (about 45 mins from Ubud center). Although it's a bit secluded, it's very easy to arrange for transportation through the villa staff.
review 2:
JdB is an enchanting place to rest, reset and getaway from daily hustles and bustles, all thanks to Dayu — the beautiful soul behind it all.

We keep coming back for her cooking – Ayam Tuturuga is our favourite! Other places might be fancier, but they don’t have Dayu and her sister in it. It truly feels like coming home and being embraced by your warm, lovely aunt.

Can’t wait to spend another time here!
review 3: Tranquil peace full retreat villa .. if that what you looking for.. this place is perfect. 2 villas with saparate family and Tv/office room with huge tropical garden,swimming pool.
review 5: Amazing… wake up in the jungle. Service is nice, a perfect place to calm down

name: nasi ayam betutu " niang mangku"
address: jl. raya, Petak Kaja, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80515, Indonesia
review 1: Absolutely delicious Ayam Betutu and Nasi Campur at this wonderful family Warung...come and eat here, enjoy the rice fields view and taste the real flavours of Bali cooking by Ibu Niang Manku! Highly recommended! This is the perfect place to stop if you are coming past on your motorbike or bicycle to or from Kintamani. Here is a chance to experience authentic Balinese cuisine.... Don't miss it!
review 2: One of my favorite Balinese Warungs.... A chance to taste authentic Balinese cuisine in a charming bamboo Warung overlooking Rice fields in a traditional Balinese village. Here you will find Nasi Campur with outstanding flavors and lots of delicious additions and absolutely authentic in every way. If you've tried Ayam Betutu or Ikan Pepes in a tourist restaurant you must come here and try the real thing.....the difference is amazing!

review 1: If want to have a meal with good view and cozy typical Balinese hospitality. This is the place to go

name: Warung Mulia
address: G8R8+26R, Petak Kaja, Gianyar, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80515, Indonesia
review 1:
We were staying on a hotel near there and decided to stop there instead of going to Ubud. We got a very nice surprise, finding and small and familiar place. The couple inside were gentle and they cooked our meal from scratch, slicing and cutting every ingredient for us. It was the BEST Mie goreng we tried on our holidays in Bali. Many people also ordered to take away but is available to eat inside.
I Hope to visit them again soon
